523
00:35:50,515 --> 00:35:54,315
But you see, underneath,
he had such a warm, passionate heart.

524
00:35:54,852 --> 00:35:56,979
<i>And Charlie's just the same.</i>

525
00:36:01,159 --> 00:36:03,992
<i>Tell me about the guy you're in love with.</i>

526
00:36:06,297 --> 00:36:07,491
Victor.

527
00:36:08,399 --> 00:36:09,491
Yeah.

528
00:36:16,174 --> 00:36:20,372
- Well, Victor is a chef, an amazing chef.
- Wow.

529
00:36:20,444 --> 00:36:24,175
<i>Yeah. He's opening his own restaurant
in New York.</i>

530
00:36:25,049 --> 00:36:29,679
<i>And that's the reason we're here.
We're meeting suppliers all around.</i>

531
00:36:29,754 --> 00:36:34,714
<i>And he's actually... He's in Livorno
at a wine auction as we speak.</i>

532
00:36:36,527 --> 00:36:37,858
That sounds fun.

533
00:36:38,729 --> 00:36:40,720
For him. Yeah.

534
00:36:44,936 --> 00:36:47,461
Well, and do your parents like him?

535
00:36:49,941 --> 00:36:53,399
Yeah, my dad. My dad likes him.

536
00:36:54,979 --> 00:36:57,743
My mom left us when I was nine.

537
00:36:59,217 --> 00:37:00,445
Oh, dear.

538
00:37:01,819 --> 00:37:06,051
<i>- Oh, dear. I'm sorry about that.
- That's okay. It was a really long time ago.</i>

539
00:37:18,169 --> 00:37:19,727
Slowly, slowly.

